$ /var/lib/dpkg

`/var/lib/dpkg` contains the dpgk database.

The dpkg database can be queried with `→ Linux/package-managers/dpkg/commands/dpkg-query`.

Files and directories I've found in `/var/lib/dpkg` include:
table { ll
  → Linux/fhs/var/lib/dpkg/alternatives/[`alternatives/`] ☰
  → Linux/fhs/var/lib/dpkg/available[`available`] ☰
  `cmethopt` ☰
  `diversions` ☰
  `diversions-old` ☰
  → Linux/fhs/var/lib/dpkg/info[`info/`] ☰
  → Linux/fhs/var/lib/dpkg/lock[`lock`] ☰
  → Linux/fhs/var/lib/dpkg/lock-frontend[`lock-frontend`] ☰
  `parts/` ☰
  `statoverride` ☰
  `statoverride-old` ☰
  `status` ☰
  `status-old` ☰
  `triggers/` ☰
  `updates/` ☰
table }

